President Trump had a phone conversation with the Amir of Qatar, Sheikh Tamim Bin Hamad Al-Thani. They discussed the close defense cooperation between the two countries and expressed their commitment to defeating violent terrorists. They also emphasized the importance of defeating ISIS in Syria and establishing conditions for a successful political transition. The leaders pledged to strengthen economic and investment cooperation and to stop terror financing in the region. They also agreed on the significance of working with other regional partners to diversify economies, invest in the region, and improve governance. They agreed to stay in close contact on these matters.